<p>This opening quote from Petronius' <em>Satyricon </em>(1st
        century A.D.) sets the scene for the poem - the Sibyl is
        an old, withered, but immortal woman who is tired with
        life and wants to die; note the similarites with
        Gerontion, of which more below.</p>
